<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
This species differs from other species of the genus by having forewings with two submarginal cells (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 139–144" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figures 139 - 144. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, male 139 head, frontal view 140 mesosoma, dorsal view 141 metasoma, dorsal view 142 genitalia, dorsal view 143 forewing, lateral view 144 antennae, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (139 - 141, 143, 144), 0.5 mm (142)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures139-144" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416804" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">143</figureCitation>
) (versus three cells in other 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Sphecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="descriptive notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Descriptive notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Wings with brownish darkening; hind wing with the angle between basal (M) and cubital (Cu) veins ca. 70°, costal margin with eight or nine hamuli. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Female.</emphasis>
Total body length 8-9 mm. Head transverse (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 135–138" captionStartId="F31" captionText="Figures 135 - 138. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, female 135 head, frontal view 136 mesepisternum, lateral view 137 mesosoma, dorsal view 138 T 1 - T 2, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (135, 137, 138), 0.5 mm (136)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures135-138" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416803" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">135</figureCitation>
), ca. 1.3 times as wide as long; vertex elevated with distance from top of head to upper margin of lateral ocellus ca. one and a half lateral ocellar diameter as seen in frontal view; ocello-ocular area shining, with punctures separated by 0.5-2 puncture diameters; paraocular and supraclypeal areas with dense adpressed white plumose pubescence, gena with sparser pubescence. Mesoscutum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 135–138" captionStartId="F31" captionText="Figures 135 - 138. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, female 135 head, frontal view 136 mesepisternum, lateral view 137 mesosoma, dorsal view 138 T 1 - T 2, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (135, 137, 138), 0.5 mm (136)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures135-138" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416803" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">137</figureCitation>
) irregularly punctate, denser peripherally and with large interspaces medially (20-35 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
/ 0.5-5); mesoscutellum sparsely punctate withlarge impunctate interspaces; propodeal triangle (metapostnotum) with longitudinal parallel wrinkles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 135–138" captionStartId="F31" captionText="Figures 135 - 138. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, female 135 head, frontal view 136 mesepisternum, lateral view 137 mesosoma, dorsal view 138 T 1 - T 2, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (135, 137, 138), 0.5 mm (136)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures135-138" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416803" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">137</figureCitation>
); lateral parts of propodeum striate-rugose; mesepisternum reticulate-rugose (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 135–138" captionStartId="F31" captionText="Figures 135 - 138. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, female 135 head, frontal view 136 mesepisternum, lateral view 137 mesosoma, dorsal view 138 T 1 - T 2, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (135, 137, 138), 0.5 mm (136)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures135-138" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416803" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">136</figureCitation>
). Metasoma with a mixture of minute and coarse punctures (5-25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
/ 1-3) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 135–138" captionStartId="F31" captionText="Figures 135 - 138. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, female 135 head, frontal view 136 mesepisternum, lateral view 137 mesosoma, dorsal view 138 T 1 - T 2, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (135, 137, 138), 0.5 mm (136)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures135-138" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416803" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">138</figureCitation>
); marginal zones T1 entirely and T2 medially punctate Pygidial plate narrow, 0.4 times as wide as metabasitarsus; T1-T4 red. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Male</emphasis>
(new). Total body length 7.0-8.5 mm. Head (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 139–144" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figures 139 - 144. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, male 139 head, frontal view 140 mesosoma, dorsal view 141 metasoma, dorsal view 142 genitalia, dorsal view 143 forewing, lateral view 144 antennae, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (139 - 141, 143, 144), 0.5 mm (142)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures139-144" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416804" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">139</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse, 1.15 times as wide as long; vertex elevated, with distance from top of head to upper margin of lateral ocellus ca. one and a half of a lateral ocellar diameter as seen in frontal view; antenna long, reaching mesoscutellum, F2 1.7 times as long as wide, remaining flagellomeres ca. 1.2 times as long as wide; tyloids weakly developed, narrowly semicircular across atmost 1/4 of the basal flagellar surfaces (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 139–144" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figures 139 - 144. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, male 139 head, frontal view 140 mesosoma, dorsal view 141 metasoma, dorsal view 142 genitalia, dorsal view 143 forewing, lateral view 144 antennae, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (139 - 141, 143, 144), 0.5 mm (142)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures139-144" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416804" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">144</figureCitation>
). Face and ocello-ocular area densely punctate, the punctures separated by at most 0.5 of a puncture diameter. Mesoscutum coarsely punctate (20-30 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
/ 0.5-3); mesoscutellum irregularly punctate with large interspaces (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 139–144" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figures 139 - 144. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, male 139 head, frontal view 140 mesosoma, dorsal view 141 metasoma, dorsal view 142 genitalia, dorsal view 143 forewing, lateral view 144 antennae, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (139 - 141, 143, 144), 0.5 mm (142)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures139-144" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416804" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">140</figureCitation>
). Propodeal triangle coarsely reticulate-rugose (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 139–144" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figures 139 - 144. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, male 139 head, frontal view 140 mesosoma, dorsal view 141 metasoma, dorsal view 142 genitalia, dorsal view 143 forewing, lateral view 144 antennae, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (139 - 141, 143, 144), 0.5 mm (142)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures139-144" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416804" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">140</figureCitation>
); mesepisternum reticulate-rugose. Metasoma (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 139–144" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figures 139 - 144. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, male 139 head, frontal view 140 mesosoma, dorsal view 141 metasoma, dorsal view 142 genitalia, dorsal view 143 forewing, lateral view 144 antennae, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (139 - 141, 143, 144), 0.5 mm (142)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures139-144" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416804" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">141</figureCitation>
) with a mixture of minute and coarse punctures, 5-20 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
); marginal zones of T1 and T2 punctate; gonocoxite dorsally without impression; gonostylus with a long and narrow apical process as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 139–144" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figures 139 - 144. Sphecodes turneri Cockerell, male 139 head, frontal view 140 mesosoma, dorsal view 141 metasoma, dorsal view 142 genitalia, dorsal view 143 forewing, lateral view 144 antennae, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (139 - 141, 143, 144), 0.5 mm (142)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.51708.figures139-144" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416804" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">142</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
