<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
It is noteworthy that the other cleptoparasitic genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nomada" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Nomada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Scopoli (
<taxonomicName family="Apidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="family">Apidae</taxonomicName>
) also has a small group of species with two submarginal cells (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2335.1.1" author="Proshchalykin, MYu" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 15" refId="B34" refString="Proshchalykin, MYu, Lelej, AS, 2010. Review of the Nomada roberjeotiana species-group (Hymenoptera: Apidae) of Russia, with description of new species. Zootaxa 2335: 1 - 15, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2335.1.1" title="Review of the Nomada roberjeotiana species-group (Hymenoptera: Apidae) of Russia, with description of new species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2335.1.1" volume="2335" year="2010">Proshchalykin and Lelej 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
